{"word":"ὠμοθετέω","slug":"ὠμοθετέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n116205\" key=\"w)moqete/w\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ὠμο-θετέω</orth>, in sacrificing, <sense id=\"n116205.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">place the raw pieces</tr_> duly on the altar, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:1:461\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.461</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:2:424\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2.424</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:3:458\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3.458</biblScope> </bibl>:—<gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"voice\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Med.\">Med.</a></gram></gramGrp>, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ὠμοθετεῖτο, πάντων ἀρχόμενος μελέων, ἐς πίονα δημόν</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:14:427\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">14.427</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>: later, generally, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">sacrifice,</tr_> <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ἀρνειόν</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0001.tlg001.perseus-grc1:3:1033\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ A.R.\">A.R.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3.1033</biblScope> </bibl> </cit> (<gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"voice\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Act.\">Act.</a></gram> </gramGrp>). (Fr. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὠμός,</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">raw.</tr_> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Eust.\">Eust.</a></author></bibl>, however, says (<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg4083.tlg001:134:35\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">134.35</biblScope> </bibl>) that some derived it fr. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὦμος</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">shoulder,</tr_> and expld. it accordingly.)</sense> </entryFree>"}]}